  "text": "Balance and coordination of experimental animals were analyzed using static rods and accelerating rotarod tests. Locomotor activity was measured in the home cage or nonanxiogenic open field. Spontaneous alternation in a T-maze, elevated plus maze, holeboard, and bright open-field tests were used to assess animal anxiety and exploratory behavior. The above methods were described in our previous publications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
